		<div class="block-contributor-content">
		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><strong><span class="smallcaps">Lad Tobin</span></strong> lives in Kittery Point, Maine, and teaches at Boston College. His essays have appeared in <em>Utne Reader</em> and <em>New Orleans Review</em>. He has recently completed a memoir (for which he&rsquo;s seeking an agent or publisher) about his midlife return to rock-music festivals, random acts of rebellion, and other teenage obsessions.</p><a href="/contributors/lad-tobin" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
