			<h2>Correspondence</h2>
			<a class="xsmall link-alt" href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">Write a Letter to the Editor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>
		</div>

		<div id="article-correspondences" class="correspondences correspondences-collapsed">
								<div class="block-correspondence" id="455">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>After I read each piece in <em>The Sun</em>, I put a check mark by it on the Contents page: black pen for good and red pen for spectacular, sometimes with short comments. Today, after reading Lad Tobin&rsquo;s essay &ldquo;<a href="/article/4691">Let the Bad Times Roll</a>&rdquo; [August 2012], I let my emotions settle for a few moments, then turned to the Contents, checked Tobin&rsquo;s memoir with my red pen, and wrote, &ldquo;Perfect.&rdquo;</p>

<p>I&rsquo;d like to ask Tobin how many rounds of revision it took to arrive at this level of exquisite, understated, and humor-laced perfection. However he accomplished it, the essay did me good.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Jeannie Smith<br>Indianapolis, Indiana</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

